        <h2 class="left-heading destination-section-heading">Old Town Ibiza</h2>
        <p>Within the city of Ibiza (also called Eivissa) you'll find the stunning <strong>Ibiza Old Town</strong> overlooking the harbor. Ibiza's Old Town consists of a massive fortified hilltop known as Dalt Vila, which is surrounded by imposing medieval walls.</p>
        <!-- Read More Read Less Tab -->
        <div class="hidden-content">
            <p>You can walk along the medieval walls of the Old Town to enjoy amazing panoramic views overlooking the harbor and the rest of the city. Along the walls you'll even find old cannons and historic structures you can explore. One of the best viewpoints overlooking the Old Town from the walls is the <strong>Baluarte de Santa Lucia</strong>.</p>
            <p>Within the fortified Dalt Vila complex be sure to see the striking rustic <strong>Cathedral of Santa Maria</strong> and its clocktower, from which you can take in views directly over the Ibiza Harbor. The Dalt Vila Old Town also looks fantastic when it lights up at night. Also impressive is the main historic entrance to the Old Town, the medieval <strong>Portal de ses Taules</strong>.</p>
        </div>
